			<p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-secondary">
				Age does not decide the schedule by itself, but it changes what the schedule needs to protect. A 5-year-old is usually between the frequent-contact needs of a toddler and the more activity-heavy routines of older children.
			</p>
