				<div>
					<h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.045em] text-primary">What Parents Often Regret When Choosing a Schedule</h2>
					<p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-secondary">A schedule should be realistic, repeatable, and understandable for the child. Parents often regret plans that were fair on paper but hard to live with.</p>
				</div>
				<ul class="grid gap-3 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary sm:grid-cols-2">
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Choosing equal time without considering school logistics.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Creating too many exchanges in a normal school week.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Not defining transportation responsibilities.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Not planning holidays separately.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Ignoring bedtime and morning routines.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Not having a backup plan for sick days or late pickups.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Constantly modifying the schedule informally.</li>
					<li class="soft-card rounded-2xl p-4">Not using a written parenting plan.</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="lg:col-start-2 text-sm leading-6 text-secondary">
					Use a <a href="/parenting-plan-template/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">parenting plan template</a>, <a href="/custody-schedule-template/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">custody schedule template</a>, and <a href="/holiday-visitation-schedule/" class="text-accent underline decoration-line underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary">holiday visitation schedule</a> to reduce these regrets before the plan becomes routine.
				</p>
